node.text:
The Dolce&Gabbana Alta Sartoria collection arouses unique emotions as exquisite silks, brocades, velvets, glass and crystals, embroideries and precious fabrics come together in a perfect melody of beauty and Italian craftsmanship. 

Watch the #DGAltaSartoria show and discover more at the link in bio. 
 
#DGLovesVenice #DGFattoAMano #MadeInItaly #DolceGabbana

Introducing Dolce&Gabbana x P.J. Tucker, the Special Collection created in collaboration with @pjtucker.
 
The American basketball player’s aesthetic combined with #DolceGabbana’s creativity have given life to two new interpretations of the Miami sneaker, inspired by basketball sneakers from the early 90s. 
 
The 100 pairs of the sneakers, signed by P. J. Tucker, are paired to an exclusive NFT - the acronym for Non-Fungible Token - digital authenticity certificate. 
 
Shop the online preview, available exclusively at the link in bio.

The new looks, inspired by robotics research and Artificial Intelligence, also pay tribute to #DolceGabbana DNA of the ‘90s. 
 
Stay tuned for the Fashion Show on Monday, March 1st at 4PM CET.

“Our job today is to bring together our DNA, what we are, uniting our vision and the vision that all young people have.” 
 
Domenico Dolce and Stefano Gabbana discuss the inspiration behind the #DGMenFW21 Fashion Show, a tribute to new generations and to the freedom of self-expression.
 

Don’t miss #DGTogether presented exclusively with @farfetch, today at 3PM CET.

node.text:
Inside the walls of the enchanting Arsenale di Venezia, the Dolce&Gabbana Alta Sartoria collection reflects the meticulous work of #DolceGabbana craftsmen, where fine fabrics and exquisite embellishments reveal an unforgettable creative flair full of amazement and beauty. 

A tribute to the city of Venice, the Alta Sartoria looks include a tank top in crystal mesh with the Ca’ d’Oro of Venice over yellow silk satin trousers, shirt with Korean collar and Henley buttons in turquoise silk twill, oversize trousers in olive green and lilac silk damask and blue velvet slippers, and a kimono in pink matelassé jacquard with floral motifs and natural landscape, embellished with hand-knotted coloured fringe, oversize trousers in pearl grey silk satin and pink, bordeaux and black jacquard slippers.

Watch the #DGAltaSartoria show and discover more at the link in bio.
 
#DGLovesVenice #DGFattoAMano #MadeInItaly

Inside the walls of the enchanting Arsenale di Venezia, the Dolce&Gabbana Alta Sartoria collection reflects the meticulous work of #DolceGabbana craftsmen, where fine fabrics and exquisite embellishments reveal an unforgettable creative flair full of amazement and beauty.
 
A tribute to the city of Venice, the Alta Sartoria looks include a double-breasted, two-piece oversize bordeaux suit in Bevilacqua silk brocatelle with an animal printed motif, finished with tuxedo collar and lapels in velvet, paired with a shirt in silk satin with an animal printed motif and slippers in red and gold worked damask, and a double-breasted, two-piece oversize suit entirely embroidered with glass bugle beads to recreate the effect of Murano “Fenicia” glasswork, combined with a form-fitting vest matching the suit embroidered with the same motif and orange velvet slippers.
 
Watch the #DGAltaSartoria show and discover more at the link in bio.
 
#DGLovesVenice #DGFattoAMano #MadeInItaly
